1
00:00:09,108 --> 00:00:11,233
[STUDENTS chattering]

2
00:00:11,317 --> 00:00:12,733
[SATSUMA]
This is perfect!

3
00:00:12,817 --> 00:00:14,942
Since all grade levels are
permitted to go on school trips,

4
00:00:15,025 --> 00:00:16,983
we can use this little outing
to gather our ranks

5
00:00:17,067 --> 00:00:19,150
and foster some
club camaraderie!

6
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:21,025
We are singers, after all.

7
00:00:21,108 --> 00:00:24,942
So why don't we all come
together in harmony?

8
00:00:25,025 --> 00:00:27,942
[RYO] Who the hell plans club
activities during a school trip?

9
00:00:28,025 --> 00:00:29,567
You nerds do what you want.

10
00:00:29,650 --> 00:00:32,067
I'll be off hangin'
out with my friends.

11
00:00:32,150 --> 00:00:34,442
Oh? You'll have to forgive me.

12
00:00:34,525 --> 00:00:36,650
I had no idea
you were so popular.

13
00:00:36,733 --> 00:00:38,858
Hell yeah, man,
you'd better believe it!

14
00:00:38,942 --> 00:00:43,233
So. These "friends." Name one.

15
00:00:44,192 --> 00:00:46,317
Well, I met this
cool cat on the street.

16
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:48,942
And a pigeon came and landed
on my head the other day!

17
00:00:49,025 --> 00:00:49,775
So...

18
00:00:49,858 --> 00:00:52,650
[laughs] A bird and a cat?

19
00:00:52,733 --> 00:00:54,650
Perhaps the three of you
could form your own club,

20
00:00:54,733 --> 00:00:56,692
and call it "The Town
Musicians of Bremen"!

21
00:00:56,775 --> 00:00:59,400
C'mon, who are
your human friends?

22
00:00:59,483 --> 00:01:04,358
Well, there's... you, I guess.

23
00:01:05,650 --> 00:01:07,942
Then, let's "hang out"
together, friend.

24
00:01:08,025 --> 00:01:10,608
[gasps] You mean it?

25
00:01:15,942 --> 00:01:17,608
[HINATA]
Aw, how nice.

26
00:01:17,692 --> 00:01:20,692
They can finally be honest with
each other about their feelings.

27
00:01:20,775 --> 00:01:23,650
[sighs] Everyone here is insane.

28
00:02:56,525 --> 00:02:59,233
[SOSUKE] You're really gonna
miss out on the school trip?

29
00:03:00,608 --> 00:03:01,858
[SAKU]
Mm.

30
00:03:03,233 --> 00:03:09,525
Angry face, frowny face, and me!
Angry face, frowny face, me!

31
00:03:09,608 --> 00:03:11,025
Yeah. You sure look bummed out

32
00:03:11,108 --> 00:03:12,650
for someone who
doesn't wanna go.

33
00:03:12,733 --> 00:03:16,192
I do want to, it's just that...

34
00:03:16,275 --> 00:03:17,858
Is it your sister?

35
00:03:19,108 --> 00:03:21,858
That's not it.
Nozomi said I should go.

36
00:03:21,942 --> 00:03:25,108
[SOSUKE] So, then there
shouldn't be a problem?

37
00:03:25,192 --> 00:03:27,858
[SAKU sighs]
Not quite.

38
00:03:27,942 --> 00:03:29,983
That's pretty rough, man.

39
00:03:30,067 --> 00:03:31,525
How so?

40
00:03:31,608 --> 00:03:34,567
[UTA] Saku probably has a lot
of things to take care of!

41
00:03:34,650 --> 00:03:38,942
Like living expenses
and hospital fees, yeah?

42
00:03:39,025 --> 00:03:40,150
[SAKU]
Mm.

43
00:03:40,233 --> 00:03:42,358
That's a lot of pressure.

44
00:03:42,442 --> 00:03:46,442
So what do we have to do to turn
his no mun times into fun times?

45
00:03:46,525 --> 00:03:47,608
Good question.

46
00:03:47,692 --> 00:03:49,858
If he could make a
bunch of money, I guess,

47
00:03:49,942 --> 00:03:52,942
then he'd be able to come on the
school trip with us for sure.

48
00:03:53,025 --> 00:03:55,108
Yeah.

49
00:03:58,067 --> 00:04:00,858
I know! Eh. And then! Tada!

50
00:04:00,942 --> 00:04:02,608
Yeah! Good idea!

51
00:04:02,692 --> 00:04:05,358
I'll compose a new song and
Uta will write the lyrics.

52
00:04:05,442 --> 00:04:08,483
You can sing it.
And then we can sell it online!

53
00:04:08,567 --> 00:04:11,900
With ad revenue
and sales galore!

54
00:04:11,983 --> 00:04:14,233
You think? Would that work?

55
00:04:14,317 --> 00:04:16,567
[SOSUKE] We haven't sold any
of our VOCALOID songs yet,

56
00:04:16,650 --> 00:04:19,483
but they're pretty popular.
And if we have your vocals...

57
00:04:19,567 --> 00:04:21,650
We'll get super
rich super quick!

58
00:04:21,733 --> 00:04:23,942
Okay...

59
00:04:24,025 --> 00:04:26,858
Great! Time to get to work, Uta!

60
00:04:29,108 --> 00:04:31,942
[SOSUKE] Hey, Tamotsu, mind if
I make some noise tonight?

61
00:04:32,025 --> 00:04:33,483
[TAMOTSU]
Sure, dude, no problem.

62
00:04:33,567 --> 00:04:34,817
Thanks, man.

63
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:37,150
It's nothing I'm not used to.

64
00:05:18,525 --> 00:05:20,108
That's it!

65
00:05:36,150 --> 00:05:37,317
[gasps]

66
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:40,650
I'm inspired!

67
00:05:40,733 --> 00:05:44,525
These are the words!
I found this song's lyrics!

68
00:05:48,525 --> 00:05:50,567
Yeah!

69
00:05:51,942 --> 00:05:55,233
[STUDENTS chattering]

70
00:05:55,317 --> 00:05:56,442
[STUDENT 6A]
Let's go grab some lunch!

71
00:05:56,525 --> 00:05:58,483
[STUDENT 6B]
Yeah, it's beef bowl time!

72
00:05:58,567 --> 00:05:59,775
[SOSUKE grunts]

73
00:06:02,317 --> 00:06:03,900
[sighs]

74
00:06:05,567 --> 00:06:07,692
Did I sing it wrong?

75
00:06:07,775 --> 00:06:10,900
Nope. You totally took my lyrics
and nommed 'em right up!

76
00:06:10,983 --> 00:06:12,567
Your voice gave them energy,

77
00:06:12,650 --> 00:06:14,983
and a beautiful song
bloomed from it!

78
00:06:15,067 --> 00:06:16,150
When he's right, he's right.

79
00:06:16,233 --> 00:06:18,275
You did a great job,
as expected.

80
00:06:18,358 --> 00:06:20,567
Your technique's
perfect, actually!

81
00:06:20,650 --> 00:06:22,608
The real problem is...

82
00:06:22,692 --> 00:06:24,900
[SAKU]
♪ We always envisioned ♪

83
00:06:24,983 --> 00:06:27,442
♪ what we'd be like
in the future ♪

84
00:06:27,525 --> 00:06:31,150
♪ The people we'd become,
they took shape-- ♪

85
00:06:32,525 --> 00:06:34,692
[SOSUKE]
Our recording space sucks.

86
00:06:34,775 --> 00:06:37,025
Not to mention...

87
00:06:37,108 --> 00:06:41,067
This kind of microphone.
Well, you heard how it sounds.

88
00:06:42,858 --> 00:06:44,275
Yeah.

89
00:06:44,358 --> 00:06:50,067
[phone buzzes]

90
00:06:50,150 --> 00:06:51,192
Hey, what's up?

91
00:06:51,275 --> 00:06:53,317
Oh, great,
you picked up! Hey, man!

92
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:55,317
I wanted to see if you were
coming on the school trip.

93
00:06:55,400 --> 00:06:56,817
Uh. Maybe?

94
00:06:56,900 --> 00:06:58,567
So, us guys in
the Singing Club were

95
00:06:58,650 --> 00:07:00,608
going as one big group,
you wanna come with?

96
00:07:00,692 --> 00:07:03,942
Oh, I know! You should
invite Sosuke and Uta, too!

97
00:07:04,025 --> 00:07:05,442
Actually,

98
00:07:05,525 --> 00:07:07,692
we're having trouble with a
song, so it's up in the air.

99
00:07:07,775 --> 00:07:09,900
Seriously? If it's
a song you're working on,

100
00:07:09,983 --> 00:07:11,442
then is there something
I can help with?

101
00:07:11,525 --> 00:07:12,817
--Uh--
--Yes, there is!

102
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:14,858
We're in the dorms and can't
record any clean vocals!

103
00:07:14,942 --> 00:07:16,483
Well, you're welcome
to use the recording booth

104
00:07:16,567 --> 00:07:18,275
in the Singing Club's
room if you want to!

105
00:07:18,358 --> 00:07:19,858
We'll be there!

106
00:07:23,150 --> 00:07:24,317
[RYO]
Got him miked up.

107
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:25,858
[HINATA]
We should be good to go!

108
00:07:25,942 --> 00:07:27,733
How 'bout you? You ready?

109
00:07:27,817 --> 00:07:29,650
Uh, sure.

110
00:07:31,650 --> 00:07:33,317
Hey!

111
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:36,442
You've got this, Saku!
Show 'em what you've got!

112
00:07:36,525 --> 00:07:37,983
Okay.

113
00:07:44,358 --> 00:07:47,567
[music plays]

114
00:07:47,650 --> 00:07:52,442
♪ We always envisioned what
we'd be like in the future ♪

115
00:07:52,525 --> 00:07:57,775
♪ The people we'd become,
they took shape in our dreams ♪

116
00:07:57,858 --> 00:08:00,275
♪ But did it come true? ♪

117
00:08:00,358 --> 00:08:01,692
Wow.

118
00:08:01,775 --> 00:08:05,067
Now I get why you were
talking him up so much, Hinata!

119
00:08:05,150 --> 00:08:06,567
Unbelievable!

120
00:08:06,650 --> 00:08:07,983
Told ya!

121
00:08:09,942 --> 00:08:12,442
--[clapping]
--[gasps]

122
00:08:12,525 --> 00:08:14,942
That was amazing, Saku!
I totes got goosebumps!

123
00:08:15,025 --> 00:08:16,525
Well, for a guy
that eats cat food,

124
00:08:16,608 --> 00:08:19,442
you've really got it together!
Might have to try some myself!

125
00:08:19,525 --> 00:08:20,942
Such a great voice.

126
00:08:21,025 --> 00:08:22,358
Now that all of us
have gotten to hear

127
00:08:22,442 --> 00:08:24,275
your wonderful
singing voice in person,

128
00:08:24,358 --> 00:08:26,942
we're going to have to pursue
you more aggressively.

129
00:08:27,025 --> 00:08:27,775
[SAKU]
Uh--

130
00:08:27,858 --> 00:08:29,275
We want you, Saku!

131
00:08:29,358 --> 00:08:31,275
Thank you. But, I, uh...

132
00:08:31,358 --> 00:08:34,400
[SOSUKE]
No, no, no! Damn it!

133
00:08:36,608 --> 00:08:40,400
Can we help you, Sosuke?
What seems to be the problem?

134
00:08:40,483 --> 00:08:42,692
The instrumental track
is weak and soulless.

135
00:08:42,775 --> 00:08:45,025
His vocals don't match it,
they're too good!

136
00:08:45,108 --> 00:08:47,442
Well, I'm afraid that
can't be helped.

137
00:08:47,525 --> 00:08:49,442
I'm sincerely sorry
our digital suite

138
00:08:49,525 --> 00:08:51,067
isn't up to your standards.

139
00:08:51,150 --> 00:08:52,525
But I promise you.

140
00:08:52,608 --> 00:08:55,983
With Saku's voice,
your composition,

141
00:08:56,067 --> 00:08:57,858
and Uta's lyrics,

142
00:08:57,942 --> 00:09:00,358
the final mix we
produce for this piece

143
00:09:00,442 --> 00:09:03,733
will truly be
music to your ears.

144
00:09:03,817 --> 00:09:05,650
I don't care how good
of a mixer you are.

145
00:09:05,733 --> 00:09:07,900
There's no way you can match
these pre-recorded loops

146
00:09:07,983 --> 00:09:10,650
to the quality of Saku's voice!

147
00:09:10,733 --> 00:09:15,692
Nothing beats live sound!
Live, live, live, sound!

148
00:09:15,775 --> 00:09:16,858
That's what I'm talkin' about!

149
00:09:16,942 --> 00:09:19,150
We're gonna record a
custom backup track!

150
00:09:19,233 --> 00:09:20,900
[UTA]
Saku! Let's go!

151
00:09:20,983 --> 00:09:22,400
On an instrument quest!

152
00:09:22,483 --> 00:09:23,233
[SAKU]
Wait!

153
00:09:23,317 --> 00:09:25,108
Sorry. Um, Mitsuki?

154
00:09:25,192 --> 00:09:26,817
Could we have the
room for a while?

155
00:09:26,900 --> 00:09:29,108
We'll be extra careful
with it, I promise.

156
00:09:29,192 --> 00:09:30,483
Please, be my guest.

157
00:09:30,567 --> 00:09:33,275
Thanks, I owe ya one!

158
00:09:33,358 --> 00:09:34,858
Good luck!

159
00:09:34,942 --> 00:09:38,233
Those three really do seem to
have fun together, don't they?

160
00:10:03,483 --> 00:10:05,150
[CHONO]
Okay, so as all of you know,

161
00:10:05,233 --> 00:10:07,317
tomorrow's the start
of summer vacation.

162
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:09,442
Now, I do want you all
to enjoy your break.

163
00:10:09,525 --> 00:10:11,858
But don't go slacking off
too much, all right?

164
00:10:11,942 --> 00:10:13,317
Your school trip this year falls

165
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:15,400
during the second half
of your time off.

166
00:10:15,483 --> 00:10:18,650
So make sure to do your
homework before you go! Got it?

167
00:10:18,733 --> 00:10:19,983
[STUDENT 6C]
Yes, sir!

168
00:10:20,067 --> 00:10:22,025
[STUDENTS chattering]

169
00:10:22,108 --> 00:10:25,275
[SOSUKE gasps]
No way.

170
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:30,942
[SOSUKE]
It's not selling at all.

171
00:10:31,025 --> 00:10:34,275
Five whole downloads, wow!

172
00:10:34,358 --> 00:10:38,150
You know those are just from the
guys in the singing club, dude.

173
00:10:38,233 --> 00:10:41,650
Maybe you'd be better off
if you just used VOCALOIDS.

174
00:10:41,733 --> 00:10:43,150
[SOSUKE]
Don't you dare say that!

175
00:10:43,233 --> 00:10:45,108
Saku, your performance
was amazing!

176
00:10:45,192 --> 00:10:49,400
You did great. Both of you did.
I'm proud of our work.

177
00:10:49,483 --> 00:10:52,817
I just don't understand
why it's underperforming.

178
00:10:55,692 --> 00:10:57,025
I'm not surprised.

179
00:10:57,108 --> 00:11:00,733
It's too shy right now.
The song is hiding in its shell.

180
00:11:00,817 --> 00:11:02,108
How can it be "shy"?

181
00:11:02,192 --> 00:11:04,192
Because it takes
after Saku here!

182
00:11:04,275 --> 00:11:05,275
Sorry.

183
00:11:05,358 --> 00:11:07,233
Will you two focus
for five seconds?

184
00:11:07,317 --> 00:11:09,400
What are we supposed to do now?

185
00:11:09,483 --> 00:11:11,317
[KAKERU] Well, for starters,
you could come down off the roof

186
00:11:11,400 --> 00:11:12,733
and start talking to people!

187
00:11:12,817 --> 00:11:14,108
[ALL]
Huh?

188
00:11:14,192 --> 00:11:16,525
So how about it then?
It's time you three ventured

189
00:11:16,608 --> 00:11:18,692
into the magical
world of marketing!

190
00:11:18,775 --> 00:11:19,567
[SAKU]
Uh...

191
00:11:19,650 --> 00:11:21,817
Who are you?

192
00:11:21,900 --> 00:11:24,567
Kakeru Iimori of the
Beautification Promotion Club.

193
00:11:24,650 --> 00:11:27,442
Hinata said you guys would
most likely be hiding up here.

194
00:11:27,525 --> 00:11:28,567
Wait, he did?

195
00:11:28,650 --> 00:11:31,025
But why was your club
looking for us?

196
00:11:31,108 --> 00:11:32,442
Heh, heh.

197
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:34,900
[music plays]

198
00:11:34,983 --> 00:11:35,983
[SAKU singing]

199
00:11:36,067 --> 00:11:36,817
[ALL gasp]

200
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:38,317
Hang on a sec.

201
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:40,650
Yeah that's right. I heard
your song while I was cleaning,

202
00:11:40,733 --> 00:11:42,900
which is our club's forte,
as you know.

203
00:11:42,983 --> 00:11:45,067
So I recorded it for inspection.

204
00:11:45,150 --> 00:11:47,525
Can't be too careful with
possible noise pollution.

205
00:11:47,608 --> 00:11:48,900
So, he's a pirate!

206
00:11:48,983 --> 00:11:51,483
A song thief who gets
all of his music illegally!

207
00:11:51,567 --> 00:11:53,108
Without a care in the world!

208
00:11:53,192 --> 00:11:56,025
What? I'm not some
filthy scallywag!

209
00:11:57,817 --> 00:12:01,025
This is my sister!
Isn't she a cutie?

210
00:12:01,108 --> 00:12:02,650
[ALL]
Huh?

211
00:12:02,733 --> 00:12:04,858
[KAKERU] I had her listen to
this recording of your song.

212
00:12:04,942 --> 00:12:07,358
She loved it so much,
she wanted a copy!

213
00:12:07,442 --> 00:12:10,567
So I bought her one,
a hundred percent legally.

214
00:12:10,650 --> 00:12:12,192
[UTA, SOSUKE]
We get it now! Thanks!

215
00:12:12,275 --> 00:12:13,650
[SAKU]
Thanks.

216
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:15,608
To think that you guys were
Utasuke this entire time.

217
00:12:15,692 --> 00:12:18,192
Your song made my
little sister so happy.

218
00:12:18,275 --> 00:12:21,858
I just had to hunt you down
and return the favor! [laughs]

219
00:12:21,942 --> 00:12:24,983
Favor? I'm not sure
that I follow.

220
00:12:25,067 --> 00:12:26,317
[KAKERU] When you're
trying to sell new music,

221
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:28,775
you can't just expect
old fans to carry over.

222
00:12:28,858 --> 00:12:32,358
You have to constantly reel in
new fans with a great new hook!

223
00:12:32,442 --> 00:12:34,567
And I know just what you need.

224
00:12:34,650 --> 00:12:37,067
The four of us are
gonna make a PV!

225
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:38,192
PV?

226
00:12:38,275 --> 00:12:40,442
You mean a real
promotional video?

227
00:12:40,525 --> 00:12:41,983
[KAKERU]
We'll make the perfect vid.

228
00:12:42,067 --> 00:12:45,150
And then we'll upload it to all
the hottest streaming sites.

229
00:12:45,233 --> 00:12:47,150
Never underestimate
what one great video

230
00:12:47,233 --> 00:12:48,650
can do for a band's sales.

231
00:12:48,733 --> 00:12:50,650
It's practically
free advertising!

232
00:12:50,733 --> 00:12:53,400
That's how you move
singles in today's market!

233
00:12:54,358 --> 00:12:56,692
But how are the three of
us supposed to make a PV?

234
00:12:56,775 --> 00:12:58,483
We're justa bunch of musicians.

235
00:12:58,567 --> 00:13:00,025
We don't know
anything about filmmaking!

236
00:13:00,108 --> 00:13:02,442
[KAKERU chuckles]
You just leave all that to me.

237
00:13:02,525 --> 00:13:03,817
[SAKU, SOSUKE, UTA]
Huh?

238
00:13:03,900 --> 00:13:06,150
Not only am I a member
of the Beautification Club,

239
00:13:06,233 --> 00:13:09,150
I'm also in the Drama Club, and
with me in the director's chair,

240
00:13:09,233 --> 00:13:11,067
this video's gonna
be a smash hit!

241
00:13:11,150 --> 00:13:12,567
--[SOSUKE, UTA] Huh?
--[SAKU] Uh...

242
00:13:12,650 --> 00:13:14,275
[KAKERU] And then I'll
show the finished piece

243
00:13:14,358 --> 00:13:16,942
to my beloved sister!

244
00:13:17,025 --> 00:13:21,567
Weird flex, but I don't care,
we get to make a video!

245
00:13:21,650 --> 00:13:23,400
I take it you're
